===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `debc` command is used for managing Debian packages (with the .deb format).  It simplifies common tasks, such as installing, removing, and viewing information about packages.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `debc install <package_name.deb>` --> 📦 Install a package from a .deb file.
    🔹 `debc remove <package_name>`      --> 🗑 Remove a package that has already been installed.
    🔹 `debc info <package_name>`        --> ℹ️ Display information about a package (version, dependencies).
    🔹 `debc search <keyword>`          --> 🔍 Search for packages in the repository.
    🔹 `debc list`                 --> 📋 List all installed packages.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ debc install mypackage.deb

    🔹 Install the "mypackage.deb" package.

    $ debc remove mypackage

    🔹 Remove the "mypackage" from the system.

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ debc info vlc

    🔹 Displays information about the VLC package, including the version, date, and dependencies.

